Step 1 : Model Setup 
#models.py
from django.db import models

class MenuItem(models.Model):
   name = models.CharField(max_length=100)
   price = models.DecimalField(max_digits=6, decimal_places=2)
   is_available = models.BooleanField(default=True)  #True = is_available

   def __str__(self):
     return self.name

After editing models
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

Step 2 : Template Filter
i. Create a templatetags
  mkdir yourapp/templatetags
  touch yourapp/templatetags/__init__.py

ii. Create filter file menu_extras.py
 #yourapp/templatetags/menu_extras.py
 from django import templatetags

register = template.Library()

@register.filter
def availability_status(is_available):
   return "" if is_available else "(Coming Soon)"


Step 3 : Use in Template
<ul>
  {% for item in menu_items %}
   <li>
     {{ item.name }}{{ item.is_available|availability_status }}
     {% if item.is_available %}
       - Rs{{ item.price }}
    {% endif %}
   </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>


Step 4 : View Function
#views.py
 from django.shortcuts import render
 from .models import MenuItem

 def menu_view(request):
     items = MenuItem.objects.all()
     return render(request, 'menu.html', {'menu_items': items})


Final Output
<ul>
  <li>Pizza - Rs.299.00</li>
  <li>Burger - Rs.149.00</li>
  <li>Lasagna (Coming Soon)</li>
</ul>
